qas.question: What is the French name of the Canadian Armed Forces?
Who are the CAF supposed to protect?
What does CF stand for in this context?

plausible_answers.text: "The Canadian Forces are the armed forces of Her Majesty raised by Canada and consist of one Service called the Canadian Armed Forces.

context: The <b4_0>Canadian Armed Forces<b4_0/> (CAF; French: <a0_0><b7_0>Forces armées canadiennes<b7_0/><a0_0/>, FAC), or Canadian Forces (CF) (French: les <a3_0><b10_0>Forces canadiennes<b10_0/><a3_0/>, FC), is the unified armed force of Canada, as constituted by <a1_0>the <b6_0><b8_0>National Defence Act<b8_0/><b6_0/><a1_0/>, which states: <b5_0>"The Canadian Forces are the armed forces of <a2_0><b9_0>Her Majesty<b9_0/><a2_0/> raised by Canada and consist of one Service called the Canadian Armed Forces.<b5_0/>"
